 This install applies to "Alien Breed 2 - The Horror Continues" © 1993 Team 17.

 This install requires WHDLoad and RawDIC to be in the path. Both can be found
 in the WHDLoad package.
 To install from a different drive than DF0: select installation mode Expert.

 The installed program requires 1.0 MB ChipMem and 0.5 MB OtherMem for ECS.
 The installed program requires 1.0 MB ChipMem and 1.5 MB OtherMem for AGA.
 It can be quit by pressing num '*' (key can be changed with Tooltype "QuitKey=").

 If you have problems with this installation please try and get a newer
 version of this package from the WHDLoad WWW-Page. If that doesn't help try
 some Tooltypes like NOCACHE, NOAUTOVEC, NOVBRMOVE, NOMMU, PAL or NTSC. If
 that also fails, please inform the author via the Bug-Report-Form which
 can be accessed on the WHDLoad WWW-Page or create a mantis issue directly
 at http://mantis.whdload.de

 For the full WHDLoad package, other installs and updates refer to:
	http://www.whdload.de/
 or	aminet:dev/misc/whdload#?
 and	aminet:game/patch/
 
 version 1.6 (xx.01.2023) done by JOTD & ztronzo:
 - AGA version: added modding options (strafe/no player block) (issue #0005948)
 - ECS version: better blitterwaits which fixes graphical glitches on A1000 (issue #0005999)
 
 version 1.5 (24.04.2020) done by JOTD:
 - ECS version added quitkey for 68000 machines (issue #0004202)
 
 version 1.4 (22.06.2016) done by JOTD:
 - AGA version access fault fixed (issue #0002183)
 - Enabled 'N' to skip levels
 - Slaves adapted to WHDLoad v17
 - Added cheat mode to AGA version (100000 credits, 99 keys, 99 lives)

 version 1.3 (11.05.2005) done by JOTD
 - another ECS version supported (only slight changes)

 version 1.2 (01.03.2005) done by JOTD:
 - support for fastmem in ECS slave (loading is much faster)
 - fixed access fault in ECS version with rebouncer weapon (Garry C.)
 - enabled original Mr Larmer trainer with CUSTOM1=1 on ECS version
 - fixed startup text in both ECS & AGA versions
 - added icons by Chris & Exoticons
 - check in slaves to avoid version mixups (ECS files with AGA slave...)
 - reworked install script

 version 1.1 (03.01.2003) done by JOTD:
 - support for fastmem in AGA slave (loading is much faster)
 - impossible to shoot on first life fixed (ECS/AGA)
 - manual included
 - source code rework and various improvements on AGA version
 - source code included

 version 1.0 (23.03.2001) done by Mr.Larmer:
 - AGA & ECS versions supported

 version 1.0 (16.03.2001) done by Mr.Larmer:
 - ECS version supported only

